cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper is about scene text recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new method based on attention mechanisms, which is a popular topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and parallel computation, which are topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with text recognition, which is a topic in information retrieval. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category.
